    "# Tutorial : Document and Page methods\n",
    "\n",
    "This tutorial shows examples on how to use some methods in the `Document` and `Page` class. All methods in the `Document` class are also available at the `Page` level. `Page` is an entity of the `Document` and is.\n",
    "\n",
    "Note: This is a highly simplified tutorial and functions in this package can be used without simplifying steps each into a line of code."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "84de4512-2b2e-4d1d-9199-c9a483006df3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Imports\n",
    "After installation, Textractor is to be imported."
   ]
  },

    "### Initialize Textractor \n",
    "To initialize the Textractor, the customer can pass the profile-name stored in their ~/.aws/config file to autoload credentials. These are the credentials to internally initialize the boto3 client. Additional parameters can be passed to the function to store output on the S3 bucket."
   ]
  },

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "extractor = Textractor(aws_profile_name='default')"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "### Call Textract \n",
    "To process an image into a single document object, we need to call an sync API. All the Textractor API endpoints support local filepaths, S3 filepaths or list of PIL Images being passed to the file_source parameter. For this example, we pass an S3 location.\n",
    "Additionally, we want a clear categorization of the document entities so we call the `analyze_document()` function with the necessary TextractFeatures passed to the features parameter."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "3f302ac5-02c9-4193-aa64-182a54c44dd0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "document = extractor.analyze_document(file_source='s3://bucket-name/acord_form_2_05272022.png', \n",
    "                                        features=[TextractFeatures.TABLES, TextractFeatures.FORMS], \n",
    "                                        s3_prefix='', save_image=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "808c93c6-ba7f-43ae-929f-33b97b8ea630",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Task 1 : Numpy Indexing on Tables\n",
    "Customer might want to access a table and edit its structure for their use-case.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Steps to perform task\n",
    "To accomplish this task, the user would simply have to:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Access tables from the document object.\n",
    "2. Choose the table they wish to manipulate.\n",
    "3. Display the results of manipulation to verify format and contents.\n",
    "4. Beyond this, the customer can further manipulate the table or choose to export it.\n",
    "\n",
    "Note: This is a highly simplified tutorial and function in this package can be used without simplifying steps each into a line of code."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b44d9f71-d05e-4fae-bdc9-d8c73267fea5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Retrieval of all tables in the document\n",
    "Table data is stored at the document and page level as a property and can be accessed as shown below."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "d65a0edc-58e8-4dbd-a8f6-4883c5859c94",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# All tables present in the document\n",
    "tables = document.tables"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "19a40312-1784-41ed-9e9c-5cb718960748",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Choose desired table among all the document tables"
   ]
  },

   "outputs": [],
   "source": [

    "chosen_table = tables[1]"
   ]

    "### Filter and display table \n",
    "To make the interface of accessing 2D data intuitive, the table filtering supports numpy indexing. Finally, to print the table contents in a structured manner, the `pretty_print()` method from EntityList class can be called upon it. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,

    "filtered_table = chosen_table[:, 2::]\n",

    "print(table_string)"

   "source": [
    "## Task 2: Retrieve key-values and checkboxes by geometry using directional_finder()\n",
    "\n",
    "It is possible to retrieve key-values and checkboxes present in a certain location of the document using reference words and direction of the required key-values and checkboxes with respect to them.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Steps to perform task\n",
    "\n",
    "1. First we select the page we want to perform these queries on.\n",
    "2. We identify the headers between which we want to extract these key-values or checkboxes. \n",
    "3. Prefix is optional. By not passing the paramater a value, we retrieve the entities unaltered.\n",
    "4. We visualize the results."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "e85b4458-671b-4770-b8e3-5a01f5e2617c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "page = document.page(0)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "b6c8abca-30f0-4753-854e-738e4da81fe6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "[LIVII OF INSURANCE (Ex Employee : $ 1600.00,\n",
       " RETHDACTIVE DATE FOR EBL : 07/18/2020,\n",
       " NAME OF BENEMI PROCHAM : Human-Centered Design Innovation,\n",
       " ACCIECAIE LIMII FOREBL : $ 1900.00,\n",
       " LIMII FOREBL : $ 1850.00]"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 10,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "page.directional_finder( word_1=\"employee benefits and liability\", word_2=\"primary location and subsidiaries\", prefix =\"\", \n",
    "               direction=Direction.BELOW, entities=[DirectionalFinderType.KEY_VALUE_SET], edit_original=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5a2de684-5533-4cbf-bec7-4724bd96609f",
   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "## Task 3 : Identify duplication in key-values and table data\n",
    "\n",
    "This function is mainly to let the customer know that some entities exist in multiple forms in the document. With this information, they can be made aware and design their pipeline to ignore this duplication if they desire to."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "eb741dd0-d4de-4350-b03b-db315967e46c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "duplicates = page.return_duplicates()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0814f135-230f-45a6-b207-92ad02b485bd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   ]
